profile_positions.description:
As Consultant Water and Sanitation I am part of the Environment and Water International (EWI) team of the International Development Division (IDD) of Mott MacDonald. I contribute to building business by assessing market opportunities and preparing bids. I work on innovative programmes that aim to improve the lives of people in various parts of the worlds, mainly in Africa, Asia and the Middle East.

Responsibilities include:
- Market analysis in the field of water and environmental engineering;
- Prepare expressions of interest and manage the preparation of proposals;
- Liaise with national and international partners to build suitable consortia;
- Deliver innovative technical contributions to proposals;
- Project management and technical support to running programmes.

As Programme Officer WASH I was responsible for developing and managing WASH
projects and programmes of Simavi in Africa and Asia. 

Programmes:
- MKAJI Programme (http://simavi.org/what-we-do/programmes/mkaji-programme/)
- WASH Alliance International in Ghana (http://simavi.org/what-we-do/programmes/dutch-wash-alliance/)
- Trachoma Programme in Tanzania (http://simavi.org/what-we-do/programmes/trachoma-safe-communities/)
- WASH & Learn Programme in Tanzania (http://simavi.org/what-we-do/wash-learn/)
- Simavi WASH Programme in Tanzania (http://simavi.org/what-we-do/programmes/simavi-wash-programme/)

My responsibilities include:
- Primarily monitor the implementation of Water, Sanitation and Hygiene projects;
- Provide guidance to local NGOs implementing WASH projects funded by Simavi;
- Assessment of WASH project proposals for funding;
- Supports implementation and monitoring of WASH projects and programmes;
- Administration of project documentation;
- Provide assistance in the monitoring of results of the team;
- Provides support to the management of relations (NGOs, consultants, networks, etc);
- Contribute to the reporting requirements of external funders;
- Contribute to policy development and develop funding proposals in the field of WASH.
